(4, 'Leadership: Leading For Results', 'Mr. Quazi M Ahmed', '6a329d25be82cd3560fc6ec0bc96734e.jpg', '<div style="text-align: justify;"><p class="MsoNoSpacing">As we know, managers at any organization only go as fast as their ability\nto lead self and their teams. If the various teams in the organization—such as sales, supply\nchain, project coordination, IT-- are not pulling together, success of managers is on the line. In this workshop,\nparticipants will learn tools and techniques to help\ntheir teams become cohesive, get motivated and operate smoothly\nto meet deadlines and fulfill their mission to make the organization\nprofitable. Participants will also\nbolster their overall leadership skills so that they can better\nlead their teams, increase their\neffectiveness as managers, enhance their team’s collective\npotential and improve performance. Whether participants are new to\nthe management role or already experienced in managing others, this course\nwill help you\nboost their leading ability and professionalism.<o:p></o:p></p></div>', '<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-style: italic; font-weight: bold; letter-spacing: 0.1px; line-height: 1.84615;">Leadership Basics: Creating an inspiring vision of the future</span></p><p class="MsoNoSpacing"><o:p></o:p></p><ul><li>&nbsp;<span style="letter-spacing: 0.1px; line-height: 1.84615;">Leaders Vs. Managers Vs</span><span style="letter-spacing: 0.1px; line-height: 1.84615;"> </span><span style="letter-spacing: 0.1px; line-height: 1.84615;">Followers</span></li><li>Top myths about leadership<o:p></o:p></li><li>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nEmotional Intelligence and Leadership&nbsp;</li></ul><p><span style="letter-spacing: 0.1px; font-style: italic; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.84615;">Building</span><span style="letter-spacing: 0.1px; font-style: italic; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.84615;"> </span><span style="letter-spacing: 0.1px; font-style: italic; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.84615;">a</span><span 