(5, 'Negotiation Skills & Emotional Intelligence ', 'MR. MOINUDDIN CHOWDHURY', '28b8e44422a3d46e3f39e5df7713084e.jpg', '<div style="text-align: justify; ">Negotiation takes place when two people (or more), with differing views, come together to attempt to reach agreement on some issue. This may be a one-off event or part of an on-going relationship. It is a form of communication known as persuasive communication. In word, bargaining. Persuasive communication is about getting what you want. It can save you time, money, aggravation and ‘face’..… or gain you a positive advantage. But there is a catch (isn''t there always?). Negotiation is a complex process. It involves learning some skills and some practice.&nbsp;<span style="line-height: 1.84615;">An emotional competency is a learned capability based on emotional intelligence that contributes to effective performance at work. Daniel Goleman, the Guru of Emotional Intelligence has focused on how emotional intelligence operates at work. He has examined the relationship between emotional intelligence and effective performance, especially in leaders. Negotiation skill becomes the best when you have a sound understanding of Emotional Intelligence.</span></div><div style="text-align: justify; "><span style="line-height: 1.84615;">So for the first time we are training the professionals to learn Negotiation Skills with Emotional Intelligence. This one day workshop will combine these two fantastic elements and equip them with all necessary skills to get the best out of any negotiation.</span></div>', '<div><span style="font-weight: bold;">Learning Outcomes:</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.84615; font-weight: bold;">At the end of the workshop each learner is able to:</span></div><ul><li><span style="line-height: 1.84615;">Pursue communication and selling</span></li><li><span style="line-height: 1.84615;">Deal with better Purchasing skills</span></li><li><span style="line-height: 1.84615;">Have skills to deal with staff (up &amp; down)</span></li><li><span style="line-height: 1.84615;">Arbitrate in much better way</span></li><li><span style="line-height: 1.84615;">Learn many business or personal transactions</span></li><li><span style="line-height: 1.84615;">Have the concept in mind always "Everything is negotiable when you are emotionally intelligent!"</span></li></ul><div><span style="font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.84615;">Learning Methodologies:</span></div><ul><li>Interactive discussion</li><li><span style="line-height: 1.84615;">TEAM Exercise through ''case study''</span></li><li><span style="line-height: 1.84615;">Learning through competence exercises</span></li><li><span style="line-height: 1.84615;">Video Clips, Movies</span></li><li><span style="line-height: 1.84615;">Q &amp; A</span></li><li><span style="line-height: 1.84615;">Program Evaluation and Assessment</span></li></ul><div><span style="font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.84615;">Learning Topics:</span></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;">1. Functional aspects of ''negotiation'':</span></div><ul><li>What is ''negotiation''?</li><li><span style="line-height: 1.84615;">&nbsp;Types of ''negotiation''</span></li><li><span style="line-height: 1.84615;">&nbsp;Strategic approach to negotiation for the Professionals</span></li></ul><div><span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;">2. Knowledge and skills for an effective negotiation:</span></div><ul><li>The 5 key stages to a successful negotiation</li><li><span style="line-height: 1.84615;">WATNA, BATNA</span></li><li><span style="line-height: 1.84615;">The 7 pillars of Negotiational Wisdom (Communication, commitment, fairness, creativity, BATNA, interest, relationship)</span></li><li><span style="line-height: 1.84615;">Effective Communication Skills with human needs model for effective negotiation for the Professionals</span></li></ul><div><span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;">3. Fundamentals of Emotional Intelligence:</span></div><ul><li>What is EI?</li><li><span style="line-height: 1.84615;">The 5 elements of Emotional Intelligence</span></li><li><span style="line-height: 1.84615;">Self awareness for the Professionals&nbsp;</span></li><li><span style="line-height: 1.84615;">Emotion Management for the Professionals</span></li></ul><div><span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;">4. Using Emotional Intelligence in negotiation:</span></div><ul><li>Self motivation for the Professionals</li><li><span style="line-height: 1.84615;">Relationship management for the Professionals</span></li><li><span style="line-height: 1.84615;">Emotional coaching for the Professionals</span></li><li><span style="line-height: 1.84615;">Creating the permanent charter for the Professionals</span></li></ul>', '12 Sep,15', '12 Sep,15', '9:00 AM', '6:30 PM', 'Lighthouse Bangladesh Corporate Program, 41 Kemal Ataturk Avenue, Banani, Dhaka', 'BDT 4000 + 15% VAT', '<p style="outline: none; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-family: ''Open Sans'', sans-serif, Arial; letter-spacing: -0.2px; color: rgb(46, 46, 46); font-size: 11.9px;">You can deposit the amount beforehand at the following account:</p><h5 style="outline: none; font-family: ''Open Sans'', sans-serif, Arial; color: rgb(46, 46, 46); margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 11.9px; letter-spacing: -0.2px;"><span style="outline: none; font-weight: bold;">Prime Bank Ltd&nbsp;<br style="outline: none;"></span><span style="outline: none; letter-spacing: 0.1px; line-height: 1.84615; font-weight: bold;">Account name: Lighthouse Bangladesh<br style="outline: none;"></span><span style="outline: none; font-weight: bold;">A/C no: 13211030031443, Banani branch</span></h5><h5 style="outline: none; font-family: ''Open Sans'', sans-serif, Arial; color: rgb(46, 46, 46); margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 11.9px; letter-spacing: -0.2px;"><span style="outline: none; font-weight: bold;"><br style="outline: none;"></span><p style="outline: none; margin-bottom: 20px; line-height: 24px; letter-spacing: -0.2px;">and then mail us a picture or a scanned copy of that transaction receipt<span style="outline: none; font-weight: bold;">&nbsp;</span>provided by the Bank.</p></h5>', '<h3><span style="font-weight: bold;">Press "Download Profile" for Consultants Profile&nbsp;</span></h3>', '658a27387e0e10cee6886f704a4a54a5.pdf', 'c552eda5a26fd6a4cbba8152370f9816.jpg', '1'),
(6, 'Key Account Management', 'Mr. Jishu Tarafder', '7286291827b286dd8a362935bc28f787.jpg', '<div style="text-align: left;"><span style="line-height: 26.6667px; text-align: justify;">Managing key or major accounts and maximizing their potential requires a different set of skills to selling. The effective and professional management of the key accounts is critical to the success of an organization. During this practical and interactive workshop the participants will consider the role and day-to-day tasks of highly effective account managers, examine proven practice in the development of an account and learn how to develop long-term and profitable relationships with their key accounts. All critical techniques and tools will be applied to their own accounts throughout the program, to ensure that they have a tangible action plan to apply immediately at workplaces. This daylong/two-day long course on Key Account Management (KAM) is specifically designed to equip key account managers with the strategic KAM techniques that are necessary to build successful and long-lasting relationships with their customers. This program will give account managers the opportunity to practice, refine and build their skills and learn to effectively implement KAM principles in target accounts.</span></div>', '<div style="text-align: justify; ">Managing key or major accounts and maximizing their potential requires a different set of skills to selling. The effective and professional management of the key accounts is critical to the success of an organization. During this practical and interactive workshop the participants will consider the role and day-to-day tasks of highly effective account managers, examine proven practice in the development of an account and learn how to develop long-term and profitable relationships with their key accounts. All critical techniques and tools will be applied to their own accounts throughout the program, to ensure that they have a tangible action plan to apply immediately at workplaces. This daylong/two-day long course on Key Account Management (KAM) is specifically designed to equip key account managers with the strategic KAM techniques that are necessary to build successful and long-lasting relationships with their customers. This program will give account managers the opportunity to practice, refine and build their skills and learn to effectively implement KAM principles in target accounts.</div><div><br></div><h6><span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;">By the end of the workshop, the Participants will be able to:</span></h6><ul><li>Recognize the difference between selling and account management</li><li><span style="line-height: 1.84615;">Evaluate and prioritize all accounts to identify different strategies required for different account types</span></li></ul><div>• Understand and diagnose key account relationships from transactional to synergistic approaches</div><div>• Learn how to move from supplier to trusted advisor and partner status with their clients</div><div>• Apply techniques and skills to build long-term relationships</div><div>• Use a consultative selling approach</div><div>• Identify and influence the decision-making units within their accounts and the levels of influence and allegiance within these accounts</div><div>• Organize objectives for every account that they manage</div><div>• Assess the potential of each account under their control</div><div>• Initiate a communications and relationship plan for each account</div><div>• Create a revenue generation plan for each of the clients</div><div>• Devise a multi-level influencing strategy for other areas of the clients’ Business</div><div><br></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;">Course Outline:</span></div><div>• Defining key account management</div><div>• What does it take to excel in key account management?</div><div>• Evaluating and determining what a key account is?</div><div>• Who &amp; what comes first when analyzing &amp; prioritizing each account</div><div>• Identifying key account customers</div><div>• Assessing the opportunity</div><div>• How do you plan a key account strategy?</div><div>• The customer perspective</div><div>• Building relationships with the entire base</div><div>• How do you manage the relationship with your client?</div><div>• Understanding the objectives &amp; needs of your client</div><div>• Re-engineering sales and service within the account</div><div>• Understanding the transition from supplier to partner status</div><div>• Staying in contact with the client without ‘bugging them’</div><div>• How to embed yourself into a client’s company by creating allies across the company</div><div><br></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;">Who Should Attend</span></div><div>This course is suitable for Middle Managers, Supervisors, Executives and anyone else who is or will be responsible for managing sales and key accounts.</div><div>Methods of Delivery</div><div><br></div><div style="text-align: justify;">This is a highly interactive course based on the application of theoretical concepts, soft skills and functional skills to practical situations that faced by executives and managers. Participants will work in small groups throughout the course to apply the learning to real issues and sales &amp; key account management challenges. Practical exercises and case studies will be used extensively during the course.</div>', '16 Oct,15', '16 Oct,15', '9:00 AM', '6:30 PM', 'Lighthouse Bangladesh Corporate Program, Level- 4,  41 Kemal Ataturk Avenue, Banani, Dhaka', '5000 BDT', '<p style="outline: none; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-family: ''Open Sans'', sans-serif, Arial; line-height: 24px; letter-spacing: -0.2px; color: rgb(46, 46, 46); font-size: 11.9px;">You can deposit the amount beforehand at the following account:</p><h5 style="outline: none; font-family: ''Open Sans'', sans-serif, Arial; color: rgb(46, 46, 46); margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 11.9px; letter-spacing: -0.2px;"><span style="outline: none; font-weight: bold;">Prime Bank Ltd&nbsp;<br style="outline: none;"></span><span style="outline: none; letter-spacing: 0.1px; line-height: 1.84615; font-weight: bold;">Account name: Lighthouse Bangladesh<br style="outline: none;"></span><span style="outline: none; font-weight: bold;">A/C no: 13211030031443, Banani branch</span></h5><h5 style="outline: none; font-family: ''Open Sans'', sans-serif, Arial; color: rgb(46, 46, 46); margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 11.9px; letter-spacing: -0.2px;"><span style="outline: none; font-weight: bold;"><br style="outline: none;"></span><p style="outline: none; margin-bottom: 20px; line-height: 24px; letter-spacing: -0.2px;">and then mail us a picture or a scanned copy of that transaction receipt<span style="outline: none; font-weight: bold;">&nbsp;</span>provided by the Bank.</p></h5>', '<h6 style="outline: none; color: rgb(46, 46, 46); margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 30px;"><span style="outline: none; font-weight: bold; font-family: Arial; font-style: italic;">Press "Download Profile" for Consultants Profile</span></h6>', '564d6187b68a6328c56b4bcd6d8f2ea1.pdf', NULL, '1'),
(7, 'How To Deliver Positive Customer Experience', 'Mr. Mubir M Chowdhury', 'a9852d6790e49d17b178b1ed4a2c497d.jpg', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 9pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 20pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.1px; text-align: start; font-size: 12pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-family: Cambria, serif; color: rgb(35, 38, 41);">It’s pretty easy to surprise customers. Just make sure it’s positive and it truly&nbsp;</span><span style="letter-spacing: 0.1px; text-align: start; font-size: 12pt; line-height: 18.4px; color: rgb(35, 38, 41); font-family: Cambria, serif;">is a delight !<br></span><span style="letter-spacing: 0.1pt;"><span style="font-family: Cambria, serif; font-size: 12pt;"><br>Delivering\npositive customer experience requires proper mindset to understand customer\nneeds and treat the customer as they want to be treated.</span><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;"><br></span></span><span style="font-family: Cambria, serif; font-size: 12pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 20pt;"><span style="color: rgb(35, 38, 41);">There are two\ncomponents two creating a positive customer experience that you have heard\nabout: “surprise and delight”. Combined together, the practice of surprising\nAND delighting your customers can net you a powerful emotional experience that\nturns into a connected customer engagement.&nbsp;But they need to work together\nand complement each other.<br></span></span><span style="font-family: Cambria, serif; font-size: 12pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 20pt; font-style: italic; font-weight: bold;">In this highly\ninteractive one day training, the participants will be exposed to different\npractical information and exercises to improve their personal customer centric\nattitude.&nbsp;</span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 9pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 20pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.1px; text-align: start; font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Cambria, serif; color: rgb(35, 38, 41);"><br><br></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: start;"><o:p></o:p></p>', '<div style="mso-element:para-border-div;border:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;\nmso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 0in 1.0pt 0in">\n\n<p class="Default" align="center" style="text-align:center;border:none;mso-border-bottom-alt:\nsolid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in;mso-padding-alt:0in 0in 1.0pt 0in"><b><span style="font-size:18.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;Cambria&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;\nmso-ascii-theme-font:major-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:major-latin">How to\nDeliver Positive Customer Experience</span></b><span style="font-size:18.0pt;\nmso-bidi-font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;Cambria&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;mso-ascii-theme-font:\nmajor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:major-latin"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n</div>\n\n<p class="Default" style="text-align:justify"><b><i><span style="font-size:14.0pt;\nfont-family:&quot;Cambria&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;mso-ascii-theme-font:major-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:\nmajor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial">&nbsp;</span></i></b></p><p class="Default" style="text-align:justify"><b style="letter-spacing: 0.1px; line-height: 1.84615;"><i><span style="font-size:14.0pt;\nfont-family:&quot;Cambria&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;mso-ascii-theme-font:major-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:\nmajor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial">Overview:</span></i></b></p>\n\n<p class="Default" style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:14.0pt;\nfont-family:&quot;Cambria&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;mso-a