(10, 'Time & Stress Management', 'MR. MOINUDDIN CHOWDHURY', '5eabde20e875ccdd2211afdf6cd32cc4.jpg', 'Lack of time management causes ''Stress''. It may cause many physical and mental &nbsp;disorientations. But simply taking care of time management can solve this problem and maximize productivity in our personal as well as in our professional life.&nbsp;', '<p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-bidi-language:BN">Program\nOverview:<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;mso-layout-grid-align:none;\ntext-autospace:none"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\nmso-bidi-language:BN">“Time, you old gypsy man, will you not stay, put up your\ncaravan just for one day?” (Ralph Hodgson, an English poet). The wise people of\nthe world always say, “Time and tide waits for none!” “Don’t say you don’t have\nenough time. You have exactly the same number of hours per day that were given\nto Helen Keller, Pasteur, Michelangelo, Mother Teresa, Leonardo da Vinci,\nThomas Jefferson, and Albert Einstein.” —H. Jackson Brown, author of <i>Life’s\nLittle Instruction Book. <o:p></o:p></i></span></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;mso-layout-grid-align:none;\ntext-autospace:none"><i><span style="font-size:7.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\nmso-bidi-language:BN">&nbsp;</span></i></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;mso-layout-grid-align:none;\ntext-autospace:none"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\nmso-bidi-language:BN">Lack of time management causes ''Stress''. It may cause\nmany physical and mental&nbsp;\ndisorientations. But simply taking care of time management can solve\nthis problem and maximize productivity in our personal as well as in our\nprofessional life. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:7.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-bidi-language:\nBN">&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;mso-layout-grid-align:none;\ntext-autospace:none"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\nmso-bidi-language:BN">We all agree that time is money. Every second counts in\nbusiness, social and political life. The frequency of success fluctuates\ndepending on how effectively and efficiently the professionals manage and use\ntheir stipulated time. Can a professional every time say? , “Let by gones, be\nby gones.” Or “Let it go at that” defying the importance of time-one of the\nmost precious elements of success. The good news is that we can manage and use\ntime productively and turn the opportunities of every moment we come across in\nto business assets if we use the KEY. Time management is a part and parcel of\neffective leadership for efficient management. We can turn every moment in to a\ngolden moment if we know the KEY. The key is ‘Effective Time Management: The\nKey to Productivity and Success’. This is a ‘science’ we’re talking about which\nstarts only with human mind-set!<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:7.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-bidi-language:\nBN">&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;mso-layout-grid-align:none;\ntext-autospace:none"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\nmso-bidi-language:BN">This is a fun learning experience for any professional\nwhere she/he discovers her/his <b>SWOT </b>(<b>S</b>trength, <b>W</b>eakness, <b>O</b>pportunity,\n<b>T</b>hreats) analysis elaborately to define or redefine the process of\neffective time and stress management for his organization to aim at something\nMORE!!!<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="font-size:7.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-bidi-language:\nBN">&nbsp;</span></b></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-bidi-language:BN">Learning\nOutcomes:<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-bidi-language:BN">After\nsuccessful completion of the workshop, the participants will be able to:<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-bidi-language:BN">(1) Have\nconscious awareness of time and its different dimension<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-bidi-language:BN">(2)\nUnderstand functional aspects of time &amp; stress management when we face\nobstacles<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-bidi-language:BN">(3) Use\n‘Time Management Matrix’ to plan ''time'' effectively and productively <o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-bidi-language:BN">(4) Apply\nthe learned Tools and Techniques of time and stress management<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:7.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-bidi-language:\nBN">&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-bidi-language:BN">Learning\nMethodologies:<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-bidi-language:BN">(1)\nIcebreakers, games and energizers&nbsp; <o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-bidi-language:BN">(2)\nInteractive discussion<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-bidi-language:BN">(3) TEAM\nExercise through ''case study''<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-bidi-language:BN">(4) Case\nStudy <o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-bidi-language:BN">(5)\nContextual Video Clips, Movies<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-bidi-language:BN">(6)\nQuestion &amp; Answer session<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-bidi-language:BN">(7)\nProgram Evaluation and Assessment</span><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:7.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-bidi-language:\nBN">&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-bidi-language:BN">Learning\nTopics to cover:<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-bidi-language:BN">1.\nConscious awareness of ‘Time’: </span></b><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\nmso-bidi-language:BN">The value of ‘time’, Individual Dependence to <st1:place w:st="on"><st1:city w:st="on">Independence</st1:city></st1:place>, Creation of\n‘time’ awareness<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-bidi-language:BN">2. Stress\nManagement &amp; Obstacles: </span></b><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\nmso-bidi-language:BN">Aligning your productivity with time, Identifying\ndifferent factors creating obstacles in time management, Creativity for\nmanaging time and stress <o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-bidi-language:BN">3. Time\nManagement Matrix: </span></b><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\nmso-bidi-language:BN">Different time management matrix: Q-1, Q-2, Q-3 &amp;\nQ-4, Choosing the right quadrant for productivity, Aligning time matrix with\nother activities<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-bidi-language:BN">4. Tools\n&amp; Techniques: </span></b><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\nmso-bidi-language:BN">Effective tools for effective time management, Planning\nfor YOU and planning for OTHERS, Essential tips for effective time and stress\nmanagement<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;">&nbsp;</span></p>', '13 Nov,15', '13 Nov,15', '9:00 AM', '6:30 PM', 'Lighthouse Bangladesh Corporate Program, Level- 4,  41 Kemal Ataturk Avenue, Banani, Dhaka', '4000+15% VAT', '<p style="outline: none; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-family: ''Open Sans'', sans-serif, Arial; letter-spacing: -0.2px; color: rgb(46, 46, 46); font-size: 11.9px;">You can deposit the amount beforehand at the following account:</p><h5 style="outline: none; font-family: ''Open Sans'', sans-serif, Arial; color: rgb(46, 46, 46); margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 11.9px; letter-spacing: -0.2px;"><span style="outline: none; font-weight: bold;">Prime Bank Ltd&nbsp;<br style="outline: none;"></span><span style="outline: none; letter-spacing: 0.1px; line-height: 1.84615; font-weight: bold;">Account name: Lighthouse Bangladesh<br style="outline: none;"></span><span style="outline: none; font-weight: bold;">A/C no: 13211030031443, Banani branch</span></h5><h5 style="outline: none; font-family: ''Open Sans'', sans-serif, Arial; color: rgb(46, 46, 46); margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 11.9px; letter-spacing: -0.2px;"><span style="outline: none; font-weight: bold;"><br style="outline: none;"></span><p style="outline: none; margin-bottom: 20px; line-height: 24px; letter-spacing: -0.2px;">and then mail us a picture or a scanned copy of that transaction receipt<span style="outline: none; font-weight: bold;">&nbsp;</span>provided by the Bank.</p></h5>', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify"><b><span style="font-family: ''Arial Narrow'', sans-serif; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;">Profile of Mr. Moinuddin Chowdhury (MOIN)<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify"><b><span style="font-family: ''Arial Narrow'', sans-serif; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;">Consultant, Lighthouse Bangladesh <o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: ''Arial Narrow'', sans-serif; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;">Mr. Chowdhury is one\nof the most popular and successful Adjunct Faculty Members at Independent\nUniversity, Bangladesh (IUB) in the Department of English. He is the\nprofessional and passionate human resource development personnel with special\nfocus on effective business communication, Leadership &amp; Management Skills,\nPositivity for inspiration, ‘Competency Based Training (CBT)’ and Social\nBusiness Entrepreneurship. He has already spent 12 years of his professional\ncareer as an expert of English Language Teaching and HRD Personnel. He has\nattended many national and international training courses and workshops at home\nand abroad. His professional attachment includes ILO, EU, USAID and World Fish\nCentre, Ascent Group, Wonderland Group, Youngone, Mondial Orient Ltd. C&amp;A,\nAuchan International Ltd. ETC, SPEED, STS, BRAC, Epilyon Group, FHI-360,\nJobsbd.com, the Prothom-Alo jobs, Bangladesh Institute of Management (BIM), The\nCity Bank Limited, KDS Group, BSRM, CSDC, Ishpahani, Computer Sources and many\nother renowned organizations in Bangladesh. </span><span style="font-family:\n&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p style="margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;"><span style="font-size:5.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;">&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<p style="margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;"><span style="font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;">Mr. Chowdhury\nis one of the first members of National Advisers’ Committee of first\nInternational ‘Supply Chain Management Conference in Bangladesh in 2011. He\nalso delivered his speech on “Leadership and Supply Chain Management” in the\nconference. He designed and assessed the first “Fast Track Future Leaders”\nprogram of 10 soft skills for the IT industry under World Bank in association\nwith ICT Ministry, BASIS and BCC for 145 participants with different\nbackgrounds. At FTFL Program he very successfully facilitated as one of the\nResource Persons of 10 different soft skills: “Leadership and Teambuilding,\nTime Management, Creativity and innovation, Negotiation Skills, Positive\nAttitudes, Professional Manner and Etiquette, Emotional Intelligence, Effective\nCommunication Skills, Problem Solving and Decision Making, Business Ethics and\nCorporate Social Responsibility”.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;mso-layout-grid-align:none;\ntext-autospace:none"><span style="font-size:5.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.5pt;\nfont-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;">&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;mso-layout-grid-align:none;\ntext-autospace:none"><span style="font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;">He\ncontinues to help and inspire people-the youth &amp; the professionals- of\nBangladesh to inspire for entrepreneurship and practice the best norm of\nmanagement &amp; leadership skills more effectively and scientifically. He’s\nthe pioneering in Bangladesh to popularize the campaign “life long learning” to\ninspire the NEXT. He believes in the adage “Together we are stronger”. He heads\nhis own brain child organization “Society for Leadership Skills Development\n(SLSD) as Lead Consultant (HRD) &amp; CEO. The very mission of SLSD is “To\nEmpower People To Enrich Human Lifestyle” which directly incorporates the\nessential concept of entrepreneurship. He regularly takes different sessions at\ndifferent colleges, universities and many other public programs namely City\nCollege, IUB, Daffodils, the Prothom-Alo jobs and so on to inspire the youth of\nthe country for Positivity and Entrepreneurship. </span><span style="font-size:\n10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:Helvetica-Narrow;\nmso-bidi-language:BN">He delivered "Leadership Excellence-The VIP\nModel" by his own research in a seminar for all honorable members of ICMAB\n(Institute of Cost and Management Accountants Bangladesh).</span><span style="font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p style="margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;"><span style="font-size:5.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;">&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<p style="margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;"><span style="font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;">He has already\ndelivered his speech on “The Theory of Positivity”, “Effective Time\nManagement”, “Effective Communication Skills”, “Improving Professional\nEnglish”, “Effective Use of Social Media”, “Effective CV Writing Techniques”\nand so forth on GTV and Desh TV. He is the writer of the books entitled\n“Learning English can be fun”, “Success, Wealth and Everything”, “Leadership &amp;\nManagement Skills Development: Work Book” and “Teaching English can be fun” as\npart of SLSD Publications. He has international and national exposure in his\ntraining, coaching, facilitating and learning approach. He is an active member\nof National Youth Development Forum, HRD Program of University of Houston,\nmember of Human Resources Boosters, life Member of BELTA (Bangladesh English\nLanguage Teachers’ Association) &amp; Asia TEFL (Teaching English as a Foreign\nLanguage), Member of BCS (Bangladesh Computer Society), Fellow BSHRM\n(Bangladesh Society for Human Resource Management) and life Member of NGS\n(National Geographic Society). He is also the first and founding Member and\nSecretary General of Bangladesh Organization for Learning and Development\n(BOLD).<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:4.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:5.0pt">&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify"><b><span style="font-size:10.5pt;\nfont-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;">Specialties: <o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:10.5pt;\nfont-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;">1. ESOL (English for Speakers of Other\nLanguages) <o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:10.5pt;\nfont-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;">2. Effective Business Communication\nSkills &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:10.5pt;\nfont-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;">3. Teambuilding for effective\nleadership&nbsp; <o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:10.5pt;\nfont-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;">4. Competency Based Education &amp;\nTraining System <o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:10.5pt;\nfont-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;">5. Professional manner and etiquette &nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:4.0pt;\nmso-bidi-font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;">&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify"><b><span style="font-size:10.5pt;\nfont-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;">TV 